        <h2>DEPARTMENT OF</h2><h3>Information Technology  Management</h3>
        <p class="dptabout">The Department of Information Technology and Management (ITM) was established in 1999 under the School of Information and Computer Sciences, offering undergraduate programs in B.Sc.ITM and B.Sc.DSM, as well as a postgraduate program in M.Sc.IT, all in self-financing mode.The department has experienced teaching faculty, modern infrastructure, and technical facilities such as a library, 24 x 7 Wi-Fi connectivity, computer laboratories, multimedia projectors, printers, portable audio systems, desktops, and a generator. The self-financing undergraduate programs have an intake capacity of 128 for B.Sc.ITM and 64 for B.Sc.DSM, while the postgraduate program has an intake capacity of 32 students.In sum, the Department of ITM has earned a stellar reputation for delivering excellence in information technology and management education. It is a testament to the department's commitment to excellence, that it continues to attract some of the best students, faculty, and recruiters from across the state.</p>
